## When to run

Before claiming site work **done** or **deploy-ready**. Pair with `verification-before-completion` skill.

## QA harness checklist

### 1) Outcomes and CTA
- [ ] Offer clear within 5–10 seconds on mobile
- [ ] Primary CTA visible without excessive scroll (hero + sticky CTA)
- [ ] Secondary CTA present where designed

### 2) Information hierarchy
- [ ] Section order matches AGENTS.md narrative
- [ ] Packages before long portfolio scroll
- [ ] Rita's Café case study before generic portfolio groups

### 3) Offers
- [ ] Package names and pricing match AGENTS constraints
- [ ] Deliverables and posting support scannable per card

### 4) Trust
- [ ] New Barnet / North London stated
- [ ] Rita's Café proof specific and verifiable tone

### 5) UX and accessibility
- [ ] Small mobile, tablet, desktop spot-check
- [ ] `:focus-visible` on interactive elements
- [ ] Image fallbacks graceful
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected

### 6) Conversion friction
- [ ] Contact path obvious; note if still `mailto` vs hosted form

## Handoff format

```text
## Changed
- …

## Verified
- …

## Remaining
- …

## AGENTS/PROGRAM
- (only if durable learning or wave movement)
```

Update `docs/design-audit.md` when completing a full audit pass.
